An overview of the principles of learning and teaching, planning and evaluation of learning, while considering a favourable learning environment, underlying national documents, the specifics of learners and reflecting both theory as well as previous and recent experience obtained during teacher training practice.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has three general aims: 1)	to develop understanding of the process of learning and establishing essential conditions for learning; 2)	to develop skills for designing learning and educational process; 3)	to develop understanding of the essence and aims of assessment.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student: 1)	understands and values the principle positions of learning and motivation theories in planning the learning and upbringing process; 2)	designs the learning and upbringing process based on evidence and values by choosing purposeful and relevant study and assessment methods, while considering students' individuality, needs and interests as well as underlying national documents; 3)	reflects on learning and instruction design as well as assessment process based on introduced theories.
